text: The Bowling Green OMS #10, at 719 Old Morgantown Rd. in Bowling Green, Kentucky, was built in 1947. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2002. It is a Modern Movement style "Organizational Maintenance Shed" built to provide for maintenance and storage of National Guard vehicles. It is built of concrete blocks and was painted white.
